* {{en}} J. Searle,. Mind: A Brief Introduction. Oxford University Press Inc, USA. ISBN 978-0-19-515733-8
* {{ja}} 信原幸弘『考える脳・考えない脳―心と知識の哲学』（講談社現代新書，2000年，ISBN 978-4-06-149525-8）

===外文===
* [http://www.ucl.ac.uk/philosophy/LPSG/ The London Philosophy Study Guide] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ucl.ac.uk/philosophy/LPSG/ |date=20090923081848 }} offers many suggestions on what to read, depending on the student's familiarity with the subject: [http://www.ucl.ac.uk/philosophy/LPSG/Mind.htm Philosophy of Mind] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ucl.ac.uk/philosophy/LPSG/Mind.htm |date=20200615172950 }}
* [[AL_Engleman|AL Engleman]] "Expressions: A Philosophy of Mind" (CafePress, 2005)
* [[理查德·罗蒂|理查德·罗蒂]], ''{{tsl|en|Philosophy and the Mirror of Nature}}'' (Princeton, 1980), p. 120, 125.
* Pedro Jesús Teruel, ''Mente, cerebro y antropología en Kant'' (Madrid, 2008). {{ISBN|978-84-309-4688-4}}.
* David J. Ungs, ''Better than one; how we each have two minds'' (London, 2004). {{ISBN|978-1-78220-173-1}}
* [[阿爾弗雷德·諾思·懷特黑德|阿爾弗雷德·諾思·懷特黑德]] ''Science and the Modern World'' (1925; reprinted London, 1985), pp. 68–70.
* {{tsl|en|Edwin Burtt}} ''The Metaphysical Foundations of Modern Physical Science'', 2nd ed. (London, 1932), pp. 318–19.
* {{tsl|en|Felix Deutsch}} (ed.) ''On the Mysterious Leap from the Mind to the Body'' (New York, 1959).
* {{tsl|en|Herbert Feigl}} ''[http://ditext.com/feigl/mp/mp.html The "Mental" and the "Physical": The Essay and a Postscript (1967)] {{Wayback|url=http://ditext.com/feigl/mp/mp.html |date=20210224134930 }}'', in H. Feigl et al., (eds.), ''Minnesota Studies in the Philosophy of Science'' (Minneapolis, 1958), Vol. 2, pp. 370–497, at p. 373.
* Nap Mabaquiao, Jr., [https://web.archive.org/web/20170331021010/http://www.vibebookstore.com/mind-science-and-computation.html Mind, Science and Computation] (with foreword by {{tsl|en|Tim Crane}}). Manila: De La Salle University Publishing House, 2012.
* {{tsl|en|Celia Green}} ''The Lost Cause: Causation and the Mind–Body Problem''. (Oxford: Oxford Forum, 2003). Applies a sceptical view on [[因果关系|因果关系]] to the problems of interactionism.
* Gyatso, [[格桑嘉措_(新噶當巴)|格桑嘉措 (新噶當巴)]], ''Understanding the Mind'': The Nature and Power of the Mind, {{tsl|en|Tharpa Publications}} (2nd. ed., 1997) {{ISBN|978-0-948006-78-4}}
* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160304105534/https://www.uibk.ac.at/psychologie/humanethologie/einfuehrung-in-die-humanethologie/dateien/medicus_engl_cover.pdf Gerhard Medicus. Being Human – Bridging the Gap between the Sciences of Body and Mind. Berlin (2015): VWB]
*Scott Robert Sehon, [https://web.archive.org/web/20121011021421/http://mitpress.mit.edu/catalog/item/default.asp?ttype=2&tid=10693 Teleological Realism: Mind, Agency and Explanation]. Cambridge: MIT University Press, 2005.
